import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]
    data['year'] = data['year'].dt.year

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='year', y='people', hue='sex', data=data, ci=None)
    plt.title('What is the trend of population over time?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(title='Sex', labels=['Male', 'Female'])
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='age', bins=20, kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['age'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Median: {data['age'].median():.2f}")
    plt.title("What is the distribution of age in the population?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel("Age")
    plt.ylabel("Frequency")
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['sex'] = data['sex'].replace({1: 'Male', 2: 'Female'})
    sex_counts = data.groupby('sex')['people'].sum().reset_index()
    chart = sns.barplot(x='sex', y='people', data=sex_counts)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of sex in the population?', wrap=True)
    chart.set(xlabel='Sex', ylabel='Number of People')
    plt.legend(title='Sex', labels=['Male', 'Female'])
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    age_group_counts = data['age_group'].value_counts()
    plt.pie(age_group_counts, labels=age_group_counts.index, autopct='%.2f%%')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of age groups in the population?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
